# Reference only — not sourced by any script. Shows exactly what
# LAB_PROFILE=minimum vs. LAB_PROFILE=recommended actually changes,
# pulled from install/istiod-values-{minimum,recommended}.yaml and
# install/ingress-gateway-values-{minimum,recommended}.yaml. Use this
# to decide which profile fits your machine before running
# `make install LAB_PROFILE=...` — see labs/lab-01-installing-istio.md.

# --- minimum (default for constrained laptops/VMs) ------------------------
# istiod:      replicaCount: 1, no PodDisruptionBudget, no anti-affinity
# ingress gw:  replicaCount: 1
# Sidecar injection resource requests/limits: lower (see
#   install/istiod-values-minimum.yaml's injection defaults)
# Suitable for: this repository's 3-node Vagrant homelab cluster running
# solo, or any environment where you mainly want the concepts to work,
# not to rehearse HA behavior.

# --- recommended (default LAB_PROFILE in config/lab-settings.env) --------
# istiod:      replicaCount: 2, PodDisruptionBudget, pod anti-affinity
# ingress gw:  replicaCount: 1 (still ClusterIP — see docs/07-gateways-and-ingress.md
#              for why this lab never uses LoadBalancer)
# Sidecar injection resource requests/limits: higher
# Suitable for: rehearsing the HA gestures described in
# docs/11-production-design.md (Istiod replica count, PDB) — still not
# production-sized, just the minimum shape a production install would
# also have.

# Switch profiles at any time:
#   make install LAB_PROFILE=minimum
#   make install LAB_PROFILE=recommended
# (Re-running `make install` against an existing installation applies
# the new values via Helm upgrade — it does not reinstall from scratch.)
